es.upm.oeg.cidercl.classifiers.refalignment

Class ReferenceAlignmentFileParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.upm.oeg.cidercl.classifiers.refalignment.ReferenceAlignmentFileParser

  • public class ReferenceAlignmentFileParser
extends java.lang.Object
    This class takes as input an RDF file in the Alignment Format, which is passed as execution parameter (arg[0]) and gives a CSV file as output (arg[1]) containing: source URI, target URI, and alignment score (separated by commas) from the alignment file (default: "./refalign.csv"). If the output file exists, the new data is appended at the end. Thus, if there are several alignment files to convert, it has to be executed several times to produce a single converted file. Command line: 
     java -cp cidercl.jar  es.upm.oeg.cidercl.classifiers.refalignment.ReferenceAlignmentFileParser alignment_file [csv_output_file]
    where 
     
 alignment_file is the source RDF file in the Alignment format and
 csv_output_file is a text file containing the alignments, comma separated
    Author:
    Jorge Gracia
